Welcome to SilverStack Nexus Repository Manager Lab! 📦

Nexus is running internally at http://localhost:8081
Nginx reverse proxy is listening on port 80 (internal)

Pre-installed tools:
- vim, fzf, ripgrep   Command-line editing and searching
- jq, yq, fx          JSON and YAML viewers and processors
- curl, socat         Networking toolkit
- arkade              Installer for additional tools
- cloudflared         Cloudflare Tunnel for public access
- java 21             Modern LTS Java runtime

Default Nexus credentials:
  Username: admin
  Password: cat /opt/sonatype-work/nexus3/admin.password  (first login only)

To expose Nexus publicly via Cloudflare Tunnel:
  1. one.dash.cloudflare.com → Zero Trust → Networks → Connectors
  2. Create tunnel → name it (e.g. nexus-lab) → choose Cloudflared
  3. Copy & run the install command shown:
       sudo cloudflared service install <token>
  4. Route Traffic → Add public hostname:
       Subdomain: nexus   Domain: yourdomain.com
       Service:   HTTP    URL:    localhost:8081
  5. Nexus is now live at https://nexus.yourdomain.com

Quick commands:
  nexus-status  nexus-logs  nexus-restart  nexus-start  nexus-stop
  nginx-status  nginx-logs  nginx-reload
